-oceanographic sensors (S1-GB beacon).\r\nThe fixed stations were deployed in the framework of a multidisciplinary research project that uses automated stations to study the marine environment, in cooperation between the Insitute of Marine Science (ISMAR) in Bologna (CNR) and other public and governmental Research Institutes. The S1 buoy was installed in 2004 at the Po river Delta and recently (2015) implemented being now an elastic beacon. The E1 buoy is off the coast of Rimini town measuring in near real-time meteo and physico-chemical oceanographic parameters at different depths in the water column. It records every  5-10-15-30 minutes  atmospheric pressure, air temperature, relative humidity, wind speed , wind gust, wind direction, net solar radiation, water temperature, salinity, dissolved oxygen, fluorescence, turbidity, speed and direction of the currents, height, direction and period of the wawes .\r\nThe data are transmitted via GSM and downloaded (on average every 2-4 hours) at the Data Center of the Institute of ISMAR in Bologna.\r\nData are daily validated and analysed, in order to be used for different studies.","keywords":[{"label":"Line transects","uri":null},{"label":"biogeochemical cycles","uri":null},{"label":"biogeochemical processes","uri":null},{"label":"chlorophyll a","uri":null},{"label":"meteorology","uri":null},{"label":"multiparametric meteorological station","uri":null},{"label":"oceanography","uri":null}],"status":{"label":"Operational","uri":"https:\/\/codes.wmo.int\/wmdr\/ReportingStatus\/operational"},"yearEstablished":1989,"yearClosed":null,"hierarchy":{"parent":[{"type":"site","title":"IT12-Northern Adriatic Sea - Italy","id":{"prefix":"https:\/\/deims.org\/","suffix":"92fd6fad-99cd-4972-93bd-c491f0be1301"},"changed":"2021-11-23T11:15:16+0100"}],"children":null},"siteName":"Delta del Po e Costa Romagnola","shortName":"IT12-003-M","siteType":"Stationary land-based site","protectionLevel":null,"landUse":null,"images":[{"url":"https:\/\